snippet.textDisplay:
I live in South Korea.
YouTube Music has been in South Korea for a long time, since last year at least.
 I paid for a YouTube Music subscription (which came with YouTube Red) since December and cancelled it in May. The search engine was fine as it was, the problem is the aut-play playlists suck horribly.
I can start with a heavy metal song, and after an hour it always ends up on pop and rap songs....
Also, artists often put in small skits and sound effects in their music videos... YouTube Music plays those parts of the songs.
It ruins the party when you're playing Avicii - Wake Me Up and in the middle of the song the music cuts and you hear "-Get up, pack your things... -Where are we going?...." Because that's part of Avicii's video...

SoundCloud has almost all of the same music including some bigger artists (TrapNation YouTube channel takes their music from SoundCloud), no ads, and it's free.

I'll be excited when Google Music comes to South Korea...
But YouTube Music is a waste of money if you like any music other than pop.
YouTube Red was OK but since cancelling my subscription, I don't miss it.
